        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[HTML Imports: #include for the web]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[<p>Think about how you load different types of resources on the web. For JS, we
have <code>&lt;script src&gt;</code>. For CSS, your go-to is probably <code>&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot;&gt;</code>.
For images it&#39;s <code>&lt;img&gt;</code>. Video has <code>&lt;video&gt;</code>. Audio, <code>&lt;audio&gt;</code>… Get to the
point! The majority of the web&#39;s content has a simple and declarative way to
load itself. Not so for HTML.</p>
]]></description>
